					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a boundary stone, east of the village.</p>						

						<p>Undated. Written in 16th-17th century A.D. characters.</p>						

						<p>States that the stone marks the boundary for three villages, <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> Kallūru <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śrīraṅgarājapuram, Āravīṭi Rāmā[bhaṭla]yyavāri-<hi rend="italic">agrahāram</hi> and Ālākoṇḍa <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Koṇḍasamudram-Vēlūru. It is stated that the Rāma[bhaṭla]yya-<hi rend="italic">agrahāram</hi> was established by Sadāśivarāya. But it is not clear whether the stone was erected during the period of Sadāśiva's rule (1542-1570 A.D.), or a little later.</p>						

						</summary>
