<lb n="2"/>mānaku prā(pra)tinā 
<lb n="3" break="no"/>mamaya(yi)na śrīraṁ<unclear>ga</unclear>rāja 
<lb n="4" break="no"/>puraṁ <g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g> śrīsadāsi(śi)vadēva mahā 
<lb n="5" break="no"/>rāyalu cēsina Āravīṭi rāma<unclear>tri</unclear> 
<lb n="6" break="no"/>piṭu(bhaṭlu) Ayyavāri Agrahārānakuṁnnu 
<lb n="7"/>Ā<unclear>lā</unclear>koṁḍa grāmānaku pratināmamayi 
<lb n="8" break="no"/>na koṁḍasamudraṁ <note n="22-c*">Figure of a standing saint with an umbrella in his left hand and a <hi rend="italic">Kamaṇḍu</hi> in his right hand.</note>
<lb n="9"/>vēlūru yī 
<lb n="10" break="no"/>mūḍu grāmā 
<lb n="11" break="no"/>lakuṁnu po 
<lb n="12" break="no"/>lamēra 
<lb n="13"/>śrī 
</p>

